<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Gain2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Gain,</orth> vb. to obtain or acquire by industry or good fortune; absol. == to profit, to have advantage: <cit><quote>despair to g. doth traffic oft for --ing,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 131" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 131</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 3.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. III, 2, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.6.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 6, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.6.193" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 6, 193</bibl> (some M. Edd. <emph>g. aught</emph>). Trans.: <bibl n="shak. luc 138" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 138</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 138" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 138</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 64.5" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 64, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.119.14" default="NO" valid="yes">119, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lc 79" default="NO" valid="yes">Compl. 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. pp 36" default="NO" valid="yes">Pilgr. 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.250" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 250</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 5.250" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. V, 250</bibl> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.164" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.5" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 7, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.1.26" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 137</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.4.137" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 4, 137</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.1.192" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 1, 192</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 6, 36</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.32" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.4.115" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 115</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.170" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.212" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 212</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.3.182" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 182</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 4, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 4.4.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. IV, 4, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 5.2.184" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 184</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.3.390" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 3, 390</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.1.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 1, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.0." default="NO" valid="yes">II Prol. 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 2.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.0." default="NO" valid="yes">IV Prol. 8</bibl>. <emph>to g. my thoughts</emph> (== dispose them favourably) <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.183" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 183</bibl>. <cit><quote>our audience,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 76</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a language,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.69" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 69</bibl></cit> (== learn it). <cit><quote>to g. the inn,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.3.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 3, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the cap of him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 25</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his colour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.167" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 167</bibl></cit> (== to restore it). With a dat. and accus.: <cit><quote>--ed thy daughter princely liberty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.140" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 140</bibl></cit>.<lb />== to make a gainer, to make victorious: <cit><quote>the foul opinion you had of her pure honour --s or loses your sword or mine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 2.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 4, 59</bibl></cit> (== will be the triumph or perdition of etc.).
